{
  "intro": {
    "title": "Verbs: Irregular Past Forms",
    "sections": [
      {
        "id": "regular-vs-irregular",
        "title": "Regular vs irregular",
        "content": "**Regular verbs** form the past simple and past participle by adding **-ed**: *work → worked, play → played, want → wanted.* **Irregular verbs** do not follow this pattern — each has its own forms: *go → went → gone; speak → spoke → spoken; write → wrote → written.*",
        "root_ids": [
          "A1.irregular_verbs.basic"
        ],
        "cefr_level": "A1"
      },
      {
        "id": "why-irregular-forms-matter",
        "title": "Why irregular forms matter",
        "content": "There is no rule to predict irregular forms — you must **learn each verb**. Common mistakes occur when learners add -ed to irregular verbs: *he speaked* (wrong) → he **spoke**; *I goed* (wrong) → I **went**.",
        "root_ids": [
          "A1.irregular_verbs.basic"
        ],
        "cefr_level": "A1"
      },
      {
        "id": "when-you-need-irregular-forms",
        "title": "When you need irregular forms",
        "content": "**Past simple:** *I saw him yesterday.* **Present/past perfect:** *I have seen him. She had written it.* **Passive:** *The letter was written. English is spoken here.* **Conditionals:** *If I had known, I would have told you.*",
        "root_ids": [
          "A1.irregular_verbs.basic"
        ],
        "cefr_level": "A1"
      },
      {
        "id": "common-learner-errors",
        "title": "Common learner errors",
        "content": "*he speaked* → he **spoke**; *I goed* → I **went**; *she writed* → she **wrote**; *they maked* → they **made**; *we taked* → we **took**. Learn the 50 most common irregular verbs — a full list is in Reference → Irregular verbs.",
        "root_ids": [
          "A1.irregular_verbs.basic"
        ],
        "cefr_level": "A1"
      },
      {
        "id": "reference",
        "title": "Reference",
        "content": "For a full list of irregular verb forms, see the Irregular Verbs section under Reference.",
        "root_ids": [
          "A1.irregular_verbs.basic"
        ],
        "cefr_level": "A1"
      }
    ]
  },
